        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>4x2 9000 and 9000i Models, with air suspension, have one back to back (double dogbone)
                        crossmember that will require bolts and nuts. 4x2 9000 and 9000i models, with varirate steel
                        suspensions, have two back to back (double dogbone) crossmembers that will require bolts and
                        nuts. 6x4 9000 and 9000i Models, with air or 4-spring suspensions, have two back to back (double
                        dogbone) crossmembers that will require bolts and nuts.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <para>Install four bolts, Part Number 414051C1, and four nuts, Part Number 414087C1, in each back to
                    back (double dogbone) crossmember (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0090401">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Use an appropriate sized drift to align the holes if
                    needed. Tighten to 75 to 85 Ft-lbs. (102 to 115 Nm).
                </para>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0090401" figsize="col-wide">
